#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""cap-plot — interactive ROOT histogram browser / plotter for CAP outputs.

Features
--------
* Browse a folder (typically histos/<run>/) and pick multiple .root files.
* Tree of every histogram inside each file, including nested TDirectories.
  Click the ☐ to tick / untick a histogram for plotting.
* Plot mode "Separate" (grid of pads, configurable cols × rows) or "Same"
  (overlay everything on one pad).
* Per-selection style: line / marker color and marker style + draw options.
* Logarithmic axes, grid, axis-range, title overrides.
* Save the current canvas as PNG / PDF / SVG / ROOT.

Implementation: real PyROOT renders into a TCanvas in batch mode, dumps
PNG, the GUI shows the PNG inside a Tk label.  No X11 windows from ROOT.

Launch:  ./cap-plot                  (defaults to histos/)
         ./cap-plot path/to/folder   (start in given folder)
"""
